  "content": {
    "cells": [
      {
        "cell_type": "markdown",
        "metadata": {},
        "source": [
          "# Threshold Splits Practice Lab\n",
          "\n",
          "In this lab you will learn how a decision tree generates candidate thresholds.\n",
          "\n",
          "By the end of this exercise you will:\n",
          "\n",
          "- inspect a real medical dataset\n",
          "- extract the Age feature\n",
          "- remove duplicate values\n",
          "- sort the feature\n",
          "- compute midpoint thresholds\n",
          "- split the patients using one threshold\n",
          "- visualize the split"
        ]
      },
      {
        "cell_type": "code",
        "execution_count": null,
        "metadata": {},
        "outputs": [],
        "source": [
          "import pandas as pd\n",
          "\n",
          "patients = [\n",
          "    {\"patient\": \"P1\", \"age\": 42, \"resting_bp\": 118, \"heart_disease\": 0},\n",
          "    {\"patient\": \"P2\", \"age\": 45, \"resting_bp\": 122, \"heart_disease\": 0},\n",
          "    {\"patient\": \"P3\", \"age\": 45, \"resting_bp\": 128, \"heart_disease\": 0},\n",
          "    {\"patient\": \"P4\", \"age\": 48, \"resting_bp\": 130, \"heart_disease\": 0},\n",
          "    {\"patient\": \"P5\", \"age\": 50, \"resting_bp\": 135, \"heart_disease\": 0},\n",
          "    {\"patient\": \"P6\", \"age\": 53, \"resting_bp\": 138, \"heart_disease\": 1},\n",
          "    {\"patient\": \"P7\", \"age\": 55, \"resting_bp\": 142, \"heart_disease\": 1},\n",
          "    {\"patient\": \"P8\", \"age\": 55, \"resting_bp\": 145, \"heart_disease\": 1},\n",
          "    {\"patient\": \"P9\", \"age\": 58, \"resting_bp\": 148, \"heart_disease\": 1},\n",
          "    {\"patient\": \"P10\", \"age\": 60, \"resting_bp\": 150, \"heart_disease\": 1},\n",
          "    {\"patient\": \"P11\", \"age\": 63, \"resting_bp\": 155, \"heart_disease\": 1},\n",
          "    {\"patient\": \"P12\", \"age\": 67, \"resting_bp\": 160, \"heart_disease\": 1},\n",
          "]\n",
          "\n",
          "df = pd.DataFrame(patients)\n",
          "df.columns = [\"Patient\", \"Age\", \"Resting BP\", \"Heart Disease\"]\n",
          "df"
        ]
      },
      {
        "cell_type": "markdown",
        "metadata": {},
        "source": [
          "## Step 1\n",
          "\n",
          "Inspect the dataset.\n",
          "\n",
          "Notice:\n",
          "\n",
          "- Patient IDs\n",
          "- Age\n",
          "- Resting Blood Pressure\n",
          "- Heart Disease label\n",
          "\n",
          "Question:\n",
          "\n",
          "Which feature are we using to create thresholds?"
        ]
      },
      {
        "cell_type": "markdown",
        "metadata": {},
        "source": [
          "## Exercise 1\n",
          "\n",
          "Extract the Age column."
        ]
      },
      {
        "cell_type": "code",
        "execution_count": null,
        "metadata": {},
        "outputs": [],
        "source": [
          "ages = ...\n",
          "\n",
          "print(ages)"
        ]
      },
      {
        "cell_type": "markdown",
        "metadata": {},
        "source": [
          "<details>\n<summary><strong>Hint 1</strong></summary>\n\nRemember that `df` is a pandas DataFrame.\n\nHow do you access a single column?\n\n</details>\n"
        ]
      },
      {
        "cell_type": "markdown",
        "metadata": {},
        "source": [
          "<details>\n<summary><strong>Hint 2</strong></summary>\n\nThe column name is `\"Age\"`.\n\nUse square brackets.\n\n</details>\n"
        ]
      },
      {
        "cell_type": "markdown",
        "metadata": {},
        "source": [
          "<details>\n<summary><strong>Solution</strong></summary>\n\n```python\nages = df[\"Age\"]\n\nprint(ages)\n```\n\n</details>\n"
        ]
      },
      {
        "cell_type": "markdown",
        "metadata": {},
        "source": [
          "<details>\n<summary><strong>Explanation</strong></summary>\n\n`df[\"Age\"]` returns a pandas Series with one Age value per patient. This is the feature the decision tree will use to generate candidate thresholds.\n\n</details>\n"
        ]
      },
      {
        "cell_type": "markdown",
        "metadata": {},
        "source": [
          "Before computing thresholds, duplicate ages should only appear once.\n",
          "\n",
          "Why? A threshold is meant to separate one group of patients from another. If two patients share the same Age, no cut point between identical values can move one patient to the left and the other to the right.\n",
          "\n",
          "So the decision tree collapses duplicates and only considers boundaries where a split could actually change the grouping."
        ]
      },
      {
        "cell_type": "markdown",
        "metadata": {},
        "source": [
          "## Exercise 2\n",
          "\n",
          "Create `unique_ages` using `sorted(df[\"Age\"].unique())`."
        ]
      },
      {
        "cell_type": "code",
        "execution_count": null,
        "metadata": {},
        "outputs": [],
        "source": [
          "unique_ages = ...\n",
          "\n",
          "print(unique_ages)"
        ]
      },
      {
        "cell_type": "markdown",
        "metadata": {},
        "source": [
          "<details>\n<summary><strong>Hint 1</strong></summary>\n\nA pandas Series has a `.unique()` method that returns each distinct value once.\n\n</details>\n"
        ]
      },
      {
        "cell_type": "markdown",
        "metadata": {},
        "source": [
          "<details>\n<summary><strong>Hint 2</strong></summary>\n\nWrap the result with `sorted()` so the ages appear in ascending order.\n\n</details>\n"
        ]
      },
      {
        "cell_type": "markdown",
        "metadata": {},
        "source": [
          "<details>\n<summary><strong>Solution</strong></summary>\n\n```python\nunique_ages = sorted(df[\"Age\"].unique())\n\nprint(unique_ages)\n```\n\n</details>\n"
        ]
      },
      {
        "cell_type": "markdown",
        "metadata": {},
        "source": [
          "<details>\n<summary><strong>Explanation</strong></summary>\n\nThe result should be `[42, 45, 48, 50, 53, 55, 58, 60, 63, 67]`. Duplicate ages such as 45 and 55 appear only once because they cannot create a new split boundary.\n\n</details>\n"
        ]
      },
      {
        "cell_type": "markdown",
        "metadata": {},
        "source": [
          "Next, the decision tree places a candidate threshold halfway between each pair of consecutive unique ages.\n",
          "\n",
          "The midpoint formula is:\n",
          "\n",
          "$$\n",
          "t_i = \\frac{v_i + v_{i+1}}{2}\n",
          "$$\n",
          "\n",
          "where $v_i$ is one sorted unique value and $v_{i+1}$ is the next unique value."
        ]
      },
      {
        "cell_type": "markdown",
        "metadata": {},
        "source": [
          "## Exercise 3\n",
          "\n",
          "Compute every midpoint between consecutive unique ages."
        ]
      },
      {
        "cell_type": "code",
        "execution_count": null,
        "metadata": {},
        "outputs": [],
        "source": [
          "thresholds = []\n",
          "\n",
          "for i in range(len(unique_ages) - 1):\n",
          "    midpoint = ...\n",
          "\n",
          "    thresholds.append(midpoint)\n",
          "\n",
          "print(thresholds)"
        ]
      },
      {
        "cell_type": "markdown",
        "metadata": {},
        "source": [
          "<details>\n<summary><strong>Hint 1</strong></summary>\n\nInside the loop, use `unique_ages[i]` and `unique_ages[i + 1]` to access a pair of consecutive values.\n\n</details>\n"
        ]
      },
      {
        "cell_type": "markdown",
        "metadata": {},
        "source": [
          "<details>\n<summary><strong>Hint 2</strong></summary>\n\nA midpoint is the average of two numbers: add them and divide by 2.\n\n</details>\n"
        ]
      },
      {
        "cell_type": "markdown",
        "metadata": {},
        "source": [
          "<details>\n<summary><strong>Solution</strong></summary>\n\n```python\nthresholds = []\n\nfor i in range(len(unique_ages) - 1):\n    midpoint = (unique_ages[i] + unique_ages[i + 1]) / 2\n\n    thresholds.append(midpoint)\n\nprint(thresholds)\n```\n\n</details>\n"
        ]
      },
      {
        "cell_type": "markdown",
        "metadata": {},
        "source": [
          "<details>\n<summary><strong>Explanation</strong></summary>\n\nEach midpoint sits halfway between two neighboring unique ages. These are the only candidate thresholds the decision tree will evaluate for the Age feature.\n\n</details>\n"
        ]
      },
      {
        "cell_type": "markdown",
        "metadata": {},
        "source": [
          "Expected output:\n",
          "\n",
          "```\n",
          "[43.5, 46.5, 49.0, 51.5, 54.0, 56.5, 59.0, 61.5, 65.0]\n",
          "```"
        ]
      },
      {
        "cell_type": "markdown",
        "metadata": {},
        "source": [
          "Now we will test **one** threshold to see how the patients are divided.\n",
          "\n",
          "Use:\n",
          "\n",
          "$$t = 51.5$$"
        ]
      },
      {
        "cell_type": "markdown",
        "metadata": {},
        "source": [
          "## Exercise 4\n",
          "\n",
          "Split the patients into a left group and a right group using `threshold = 51.5`.\n",
          "\n",
          "Use `Age <= threshold` for the left group."
        ]
      },
      {
        "cell_type": "code",
        "execution_count": null,
        "metadata": {},
        "outputs": [],
        "source": [
          "threshold = 51.5\n",
          "\n",
          "left_group = ...\n",
          "right_group = ...\n",
          "\n",
          "print(left_group)\n",
          "print(right_group)"
        ]
      },
      {
        "cell_type": "markdown",
        "metadata": {},
        "source": [
          "<details>\n<summary><strong>Hint 1</strong></summary>\n\nUse boolean indexing on `df` to keep only the rows that match a condition.\n\n</details>\n"
        ]
      },
      {
        "cell_type": "markdown",
        "metadata": {},
        "source": [
          "<details>\n<summary><strong>Hint 2</strong></summary>\n\nThe left group uses `df[\"Age\"] <= threshold`. The right group uses `df[\"Age\"] > threshold`.\n\n</details>\n"
        ]
      },
      {
        "cell_type": "markdown",
        "metadata": {},
        "source": [
          "<details>\n<summary><strong>Solution</strong></summary>\n\n```python\nthreshold = 51.5\n\nleft_group = df[df[\"Age\"] <= threshold]\nright_group = df[df[\"Age\"] > threshold]\n\nprint(left_group)\nprint(right_group)\n```\n\n</details>\n"
        ]
      },
      {
        "cell_type": "markdown",
        "metadata": {},
        "source": [
          "<details>\n<summary><strong>Explanation</strong></summary>\n\nPatients with Age ≤ 51.5 form the **left child**. Patients with Age > 51.5 form the **right child**. At this stage we are only dividing the data — not judging whether the split is good or bad.\n\n</details>\n"
        ]
      },
      {
        "cell_type": "markdown",
        "metadata": {},
        "source": [
          "At this stage, only the **groups** matter.\n",
          "\n",
          "We are **not** calculating Gini impurity yet. Threshold splits only answer: *where is the tree allowed to split?*"
        ]
      },
      {
        "cell_type": "code",
        "execution_count": null,
        "metadata": {},
        "outputs": [],
        "source": [
          "print(len(left_group))\n",
          "print(len(right_group))"
        ]
      },
      {
        "cell_type": "markdown",
        "metadata": {},
        "source": [
          "## Reflection Questions\n",
          "\n",
          "1. Why do we use the midpoint instead of Age = 45?\n",
          "2. Would Age = 46 produce the same partition?\n",
          "3. If we moved the threshold to 54, which patients would change groups?\n",
          "4. Does Threshold Splits decide which split is best?"
        ]
      },
      {
        "cell_type": "code",
        "execution_count": null,
        "metadata": {},
        "outputs": [],
        "source": [
          "# Optional visualization\n",
          "\n",
          "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
          "\n",
          "threshold = 51.5\n",
          "\n",
          "no_disease = df[df[\"Heart Disease\"] == 0]\n",
          "has_disease = df[df[\"Heart Disease\"] == 1]\n",
          "\n",
          "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 5))\n",
          "\n",
          "ax.scatter(\n",
          "    no_disease[\"Age\"],\n",
          "    no_disease[\"Resting BP\"],\n",
          "    color=\"blue\",\n",
          "    label=\"No Disease\",\n",
          "    s=80,\n",
          ")\n",
          "ax.scatter(\n",
          "    has_disease[\"Age\"],\n",
          "    has_disease[\"Resting BP\"],\n",
          "    color=\"red\",\n",
          "    label=\"Disease\",\n",
          "    s=80,\n",
          ")\n",
          "ax.axvline(threshold, linestyle=\"--\", color=\"black\", label=f\"Threshold = {threshold}\")\n",
          "\n",
          "ax.set_xlabel(\"Age\")\n",
          "ax.set_ylabel(\"Resting Blood Pressure\")\n",
          "ax.set_title(\"Heart Disease Patients by Age and Resting BP\")\n",
          "ax.legend()\n",
          "plt.show()"
        ]
      }
    ],
